      <th>0</th>
      <td>Error message</td>
      <td>Description and recommended actions</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>Cannot resolve hostname</td>
      <td>The FQDN you entered for the syslog server could not be resolved to an IP\naddress.\n1. Check the hostname you entered. If you entered an IP address, make sure it\nis a valid IP address in W.X.Y.Z ("dotted decimal") notation.\n2. Check that the DNS servers are configured correctly.\n3. Confirm that each node can access the IP addresses for the DNS server.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Connection refused</td>
      <td>A TCP or TLS connection to the syslog server was refused. There might be no\nservice listening on the TCP or TLS port for the host, or a firewall might be\nblocking access.\n1. Check that you entered the correct FQDN or IP address, port, and protocol for\nthe syslog server.\n2. Confirm that the host for the syslog service is running a syslog daemon that is\nlistening on the specified port.\n3. Confirm that a firewall is not blocking access to TCP/TLS connections from\nthe nodes to the IP and port of the syslog server.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
